review_blob: Where do i start one of my current favorite ipas. Crisp citrus zestiness and smooth with it. Winner.

Wow what a pale ale, as soon as I popped the cap the hops hit me.lovely golden glass of ale from the bottle and the nose is hoppy and crisp.on taste its a winner, fruity malty and bitter, the hops just sing for me in this beer, I love it.

I like this one,good hoppy profile and i like the citrus zing in the tail.Good malt flavours coming through the more of it i drink.Not much of a head and well carbonated maybe a little to much but all in all a good IPA in my opinion.
Nice dark beer.definate fruitiness in the aftertatste, apple for me and maybe a bit oaky.There is a real alcohol kick to this one.I like it.
Nice hoppy bitterness, not much of a nose but good flavour profile,looks good in the glass and goes down easy,all in all a nice ale.
